problem:
Coplanar squares $ABGH$ and $BCDF$ are adjacent, with $CD = 776770$ units and $AH = 865$ units. Point $E$ is on segments $AD$ and $GB$. What is the area of triangle $ABE$, in square units? Express your answer as a common fraction.

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(865,0)--(865,865)--(0,865)--(0,0)--cycle,linewidth(2));
draw((865,0)--(777635,0)--(777635,776770)--(865,776770)--(865,0)--cycle,linewidth(2));

draw((0,0)--(777635,776770),linewidth(2));

filldraw((0,0)--(865,0)--(865,776770/899)--(0,0)--cycle,gray,linewidth(2));

label("A",(0,0),SW);
label("B",(865,0),S);
label("C",(777635,0),SE);
label("D",(777635,776770),NE);
label("E",(865,776770/899),SE);
label("F",(865,776770),NW);
label("G",(865,865),NW);
label("H",(0,865),NW);
[/asy]
